<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="325" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="46.[2007,2600,1159,1585]" lastBlockId="46.[1391,2598,1591,2018]" pageId="46" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2007,2248,1403,1428]" pageId="46" pageNumber="325">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 92-115 mm, tail 24-39 mm, ear 12-15 mm, hindfoot 16— 20 mm; weight 26-48 g. Back of the Linzhi Mountain Vole is black-brown, which blends into black-gray underpart. Dorsal tail is black-brown, and undersideis light gray-white. Forelimbs are black-gray, and hindlimbs are dark gray. Females have eight mammae. Skull is robust, with straight dorsal profile. Temporal ridges are very distinct and mergeto interorbital crest. M, has five closed triangles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="325" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="46.[1391,2598,1591,2018]" pageId="46" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1394,1505,1709,1742]" pageId="46" pageNumber="325">Habitat.</emphasis>
Abandoned farmland and along footpath ofrice field where highland barley was grown at elevations of 3640-3890 m.
</paragraph>
